What would you do if your dreams came true and in the same instant they slipped through your fingers? Would you try to hold on? Or, would you accept your fate and let go?

The crown is yours. You've worked your entire life for this moment. Are you going to let it wash away? Or are you going to smile through the tears and enjoy your last moment? And say to yourself, "I won".

Inspired by @thelastofus 

The crew:
Photographer/Concept: @free_berto @ptcameraguy 
Model: @michellefortheculture 
MUA: @itzedejesus 
Stylist/Dress customization: @mandohbstylin 
BTS: @your.royal.freshness 
Assistant: @abimthedream

After watching the first episode of @thelastofus , I started to wonder what everyone else’s life was like when the plague took over. I then had this idea of a beauty queen winning a pageant. The ultimate peak of her career. Everything she had been working for finally happened. And then the world comes to an end. I wanted to capture that moment when she realizes it’s all coming to end. To see her fighting for every moment of that glory before it is all over.
.
.
This was something new for me and I really want to thank my team for helping me with this. 
Huge shout out to
Model @michellefortheculture 
MUA: @itzedejesus 
Stylist/ Dress customization: @mandoh @mandohbstylin 
BTS @your.royal.freshness 
Assistant @abimthedream 
.
This shoot felt so special and I have to thank the team for believing in the vision!

The Good Food Gurus invite you to “A Good Giving Christmas”.

This is our FOURTH year! Thank you to everyone who donated last year and helped us give to @lalgbtcenter @myfriendsplace and @themidnightmission 

We were able to create 200 bags of necessities alongside 200 acai bowls donated by Ubatuba, and products from Garnier and ORS. This year we are going even bigger!

This holiday season we are inviting you to give back a little and make someone’s holiday special. We are holding an online donation drive for homeless individuals and others in need. 100% of all proceeds will be used for our cause. We are collecting funds to develop gift bags to be delivered around Los Angeles at the end of December. This year has been very hard for many people. A little blessing can go a long way.

We are also asking for monetary, food, SHOES, and toiletry donations.

CURRENT BRAND PARTNERSHIPS:
Dude Wipes
Boxed Water
Bombas
Garnier
